definitions.definition: Acting together; collaborative.
Any acyclic saturated hydrocarbon (e.g., methane, ethane, etc.).
definitions.example: The carbon chain of an alkane may be linear or branched, but must not contain loops (cycles); its chemical formula is of the form CnH2n+2.
